section.def:
mine
                (礦場) includes any place, excavation or working
            whereon, wherein or whereby an operation in connexion with mining is carried on;

regulations
                (規例) means any regulations for the time being in
            force, made under the provisions of this Ordinance;

Superintendent
                (總監) means the Superintendent of Mines appointed
            under the provisions of section 42;

paragraph.content:
the person, if any, who is carrying on or has carried on under licence
                        adequate prospecting or mining operations on the area shall be preferred;
                        and

prepare and render such records, reports and returns as may be prescribed by
                the regulations or as may be required by the Commissioner or the Chief Executive;
                and

prospects, save under the authority of, and in
                                                accordance with the terms and conditions of, a valid
                                                prospecting licence;

mines, save under the authority of, and in accordance
                                                with the terms and conditions of, a valid mining
                                                licence or mining lease;

prospects or mines on any of the lands mentioned in
                                                  section 9 without the requisite
                                                authority;

the fencing off or rendering secure of any shaft, tunnel, well, trench,
                    drive or other works constructed or made for prospecting or mining
                    purposes;

the returns to be rendered and the accounts, registers, books and plans to
                    be kept by the holders of prospecting licences, mining licences and mining
                    leases;

the safety, welfare, health and housing conditions of persons employed in
                    mining operations and the carrying on of prospecting or mining operations in a
                    safe, sanitary, proper, economic and effectual manner;
